    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Words of Mormon",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "Mormon abridges the large plates of Nephi\u2014He puts the small plates with the other plates\u2014King Benjamin establishes peace in the land. About A.D.\u00a0385.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And now I, Mormon, being about to deliver up the record which I have been making into the hands of my son Moroni, behold I have witnessed almost all the destruction of my people, the Nephites.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 5:12 (9\u201312); Morm. 1:4 (1\u20134); 2:17 (17\u201318); 8:5 (1, 4\u20135, 14).",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it is many hundred years after the coming of Christ that I deliver these records into the hands of my son; and it supposeth me that he will witness the entire destruction of my people. But may God grant that he may survive them, that he may write somewhat concerning them, and somewhat concerning Christ, that perhaps some day it may profit them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 6:5 (5\u20136).",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 12:19.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 174
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 3:19 (16\u201320).",
                        "start": 338,
                        "end": 344
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, I speak somewhat concerning that which I have written; for after I had made an abridgment from the plates of Nephi, down to the reign of this king Benjamin, of whom Amaleki spake, I searched among the records which had been delivered into my hands, and I found these plates, which contained this small account of the prophets, from Jacob down to the reign of this king Benjamin, and also many of the words of Nephi.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 1:17 (16\u201317); D&C 10:44.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jarom 1:14; W\u00a0of\u00a0M 1:10; D&C 10:38 (38\u201340).",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 1:6 (2\u20136); Hel. 3:13 (13\u201315); Morm. 4:23.",
                        "start": 210,
                        "end": 217
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Omni 1:23 (23\u201325).",
                        "start": 378,
                        "end": 386
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the things which are upon these plates pleasing me, because of the prophecies of the coming of Christ; and my fathers knowing that many of them have been fulfilled; yea, and I also know that as many things as have been prophesied concerning us down to this day have been fulfilled, and as many as go beyond this day must surely come to pass\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 6:5 (3\u20136).",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Prophecies about.",
                        "start": 223,
                        "end": 233
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, I chose these things, to finish my record upon them, which remainder of my record I shall take from the plates of Nephi; and I cannot write the hundredth part of the things of my people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the things pleasing to him, mentioned in v.\u00a04.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 5:17 (14\u201318); Morm. 1:1.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:2.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 130
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 13:31; 3\u00a0Ne. 5:8 (8\u201311); 26:6 (6\u201312).",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But behold, I shall take these plates, which contain these prophesyings and revelations, and put them with the remainder of my record, for they are choice unto me; and I know they will be choice unto my brethren.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 144
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I do this for a wise purpose; for thus it whispereth me, according to the workings of the Spirit of the Lord which is in me. And now, I do not know all things; but the Lord knoweth all things which are to come; wherefore, he worketh in me to do according to his will.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:5; 19:3; Enos 1:13 (13\u201318); Alma 37:2; D&C 3:19 (9\u201320); 10:34 (1\u201319, 30\u201347).",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 10:40 (20\u201346).",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Foreknowledge of; God, Intelligence of; God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 177,
                        "end": 184
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 27:23.",
                        "start": 229,
                        "end": 236
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Will of.",
                        "start": 266,
                        "end": 270
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And my prayer to God is concerning my brethren, that they may once again come to the knowledge of God, yea, the redemption of Christ; that they may once again be a delightsome people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 33:3; Enos 1:11 (11\u201312); Moro. 9:22.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 30:6.",
                        "start": 164,
                        "end": 175
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now I, Mormon, proceed to finish out my record, which I take from the plates of Nephi; and I make it according to the knowledge and the understanding which God has given me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 153
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, it came to pass that after Amaleki had delivered up these plates into the hands of king Benjamin, he took them and put them with the other plates, which contained records which had been handed down by the kings, from generation to generation until the days of king Benjamin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Omni 1:25 (25, 30).",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:4; Omni 1:11, 18; W\u00a0of\u00a0M 1:3; Mosiah 28:11.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 156
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jarom 1:14.",
                        "start": 216,
                        "end": 221
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they were handed down from king Benjamin, from generation to generation until they have fallen into my hands. And I, Mormon, pray to God that they may be preserved from this time henceforth. And I know that they will be preserved; for there are great things written upon them, out of which my people and their brethren shall be judged at the great and last day, according to the word of God which is written.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 5:12 (8\u201312); Morm. 1:4 (1\u20135).",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 15:3 (3\u20134).",
                        "start": 294,
                        "end": 296
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 25:18; 29:11; 33:14 (11, 14\u201315); 3\u00a0Ne. 27:25 (23\u201327); Ether 5:4.",
                        "start": 332,
                        "end": 338
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, concerning this king Benjamin\u2014he had somewhat of contentions among his own people.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass also that the armies of the Lamanites came down out of the land of Nephi, to battle against his people. But behold, king Benjamin gathered together his armies, and he did stand against them; and he did fight with the strength of his own arm, with the sword of Laban.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Omni 1:12.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 4:9; 2\u00a0Ne. 5:14; Jacob 1:10; Mosiah 1:16; D&C 17:1.",
                        "start": 271,
                        "end": 276
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in the strength of the Lord they did contend against their enemies, until they had slain many thousands of the Lamanites. And it came to pass that they did contend against the Lamanites until they had driven them out of all the lands of their inheritance.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strength.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jarom 1:7.",
                        "start": 247,
                        "end": 258
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that after there had been false Christs, and their mouths had been shut, and they punished according to their crimes;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Christs.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And after there had been false prophets, and false preachers and teachers among the people, and all these having been punished according to their crimes; and after there having been much contention and many dissensions away unto the Lamanites, behold, it came to pass that king Benjamin, with the assistance of the holy prophets who were among his people\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Prophets.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 1:14 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 224,
                        "end": 228
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Enos 1:22.",
                        "start": 320,
                        "end": 328
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, king Benjamin was a holy man, and he did reign over his people in righteousness; and there were many holy men in the land, and they did speak the word of God with power and with authority; and they did use much sharpness because of the stiffneckedness of the people\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 22:31; Alma 13:26; D&C 49:8; 107:29.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 17:3 (2\u20133). TG\u00a0God, Power of.",
                        "start": 175,
                        "end": 180
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Enos 1:23; Moro. 9:4; D&C 121:43 (41\u201343).",
                        "start": 223,
                        "end": 232
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 145
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, with the help of these, king Benjamin, by laboring with all the might of his body and the faculty of his whole soul, and also the prophets, did once more establish peace in the land.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Omni 1:25; Mosiah 29:13.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:25.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}